sentences: Reverend Maceo Len Woods (April 23, 1932 â€“ January 11, 2020), was an American gospel musician and noted organist, who founded, Christian Tabernacle Church.
He started his music career, in 1954, with the release of, Amazing Grace, that was released by Vee-Jay Records.

His 25 releases have spanned the course of 50 plus years in recording music, and he has released albums with a myriad of noteworthy labels including; Vee-Jay Records, Volt Records, Arista Records, P-Vine Records, and Stax Records.

Reverend Woods was born on April 23, 1932 in Chicago, Illinois as Maceo Len Woods, and he is a celebrated organist, who founded Christian Tabernacle Church that is located on Prairie Avenue in Chicago.
